The paper discusses mathematical connections between market scoring rules, cost function based prediction markets, and no-regret learning. These topics are all related to game theory, machine learning, and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the CS sub-categories of cs.GT, cs.LG, and cs.AI. The paper also involves the analysis of data and algorithms, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.DS and cs.EC. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
